A conversation between M·A·C Trainer @marcsinclairmua and @microrainbow Founder and CEO Sebastian Rocca about the phenomenal work they do and how M·A·C is supporting and collaborating with this. 

This Pride, M·A·C donates £50,000 to Micro Rainbow, supporting the purchase of a safe house in the UK for LGBTQI asylum seekers and refugees fleeing persecution.
The donation is funded from M·A·C Cosmetics’ long-standing VIVA GLAM campaign, which was created in 1994 and sees 100% of the sales, less VAT, of all VIVA GLAM Lipsticks in the UK and Ireland go towards to organisations that support the health and rights of people of All Ages, All Races and All Genders.

latestPosts.caption:
Proud. Loud. Unstoppable 💄💋 M•A•C served looks and love at #londonpride, marching the parade with our Viva Glam charity partner @positiveeast 

But Pride is more than a party. 💪 Since 1994, every penny of the selling price of #VIVAGLAM lipsticks has gone to support healthy futures and equal rights for all. That’s over $500 million raised to fight HIV/AIDS and support LGBTQIA+ communities worldwide. 💖

When you wear VIVA GLAM, you’re not just making a statement… you’re making a difference. 

@positiveeast support those effected and living with HIV, it was an honour to march with them for PRIDE 🏳️‍🌈🏳️‍⚧️

A recap of Drag Raise with our Viva Glam charity partners @nationalaidstrust ❤️ Last night we donated £75,000 to @nationalaidstrust - all thanks to Viva Glam! 

(we also delivered some iconic lip combos using Viva Glam Lipstick & Lipglass Air the entire evening) 💋💄

National AIDS Trust are a charity we are proud to sponsor, fighting the stigma of HIV & AIDS and on a mission to end new HIV transmissions by 2030! 

With Viva Glam we give back 100% to our charity partners supporting sexual, gender, racial and environmental equality. Remember… our lipsticks save lives! 💋❤️ 

#macvivaglam #vivaglam #dragraise #nationalaidstrust
